When people meet my fur kids I am often asked if I picked them based on their color since they all three match. I was awakened by Piko's plaintive cries outside my apartment in Ishiyama, Japan back in 2000. A coworker in Maine in 2002 asked if I would take in a cat her brother found; of course I had to say "yes" when I saw Lucy was a tortie like Piko. I had no intention of adopting a dog when I met @corbinthekelpie @lexingtonhumane while leading some teen volunteers. He had just come down to the adoption floor and was timid and wouldn't come out of his kennel for the kids so I stayed after to work with him and then came early/stayed late following sessions until I couldn't bear the thought of him with anyone other than me. üòç And here we are, one big happy family.

AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION!!! Meet Bradford a super handsome Hound/Shepherd mix born around 2009. Bradford was recently abandoned at a local shelter alone and afraid. He is now safe and warm in his foster home and adjusting well. Bradford is a calm, well-mannered and very attentive boy. He absolutely loves everyone he meets!!! He is house trained and rides great in the car. He is great with other dogs. He enjoys napping in the sun and chasing squirrels in the yard. He knows basic commands such as come, sit and lie down. He is current on vaccines, neutered and microchipped. He currently weighs 64lbs and is full grown. Bradford will make a very loyal companion, and is now looking for a forever home.
